# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# .gitignore for the vqe-hydrogen Qiskit project.
#
# This file tells git which paths to IGNORE when staging/committing.
# It is read by git itself (not by Python), every time you run `git add`,
# `git status`, etc. It has no runtime effect on the program.
#
# We ignore three categories:
#   1. Python build/runtime artifacts (regenerated by Python/pip).
#   2. Qiskit / Jupyter artifacts and credentials (must never be committed).
#   3. Editor and OS noise (machine-specific, not part of the project).
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------


# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 1. Python build / runtime artifacts
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Byte-compiled / optimized / DLL files produced by the CPython interpreter
# whenever a module is imported. Always regenerated, never source.
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*$py.class

# C extensions compiled from Python sources.
*.so

# Distribution / packaging output from `python -m build`, `setup.py`, etc.
# These are build artifacts, not source.
build/
dist/
*.egg-info/
*.egg
.eggs/
wheels/
pip-wheel-metadata/
MANIFEST

# Installer logs produced by pip when it errors out.
pip-log.txt
pip-delete-this-directory.txt

# Unit test / coverage reports. Regenerated by `pytest`, `coverage`, etc.
htmlcov/
.tox/
.nox/
.coverage
.coverage.*
.cache
.pytest_cache/
.mypy_cache/
.ruff_cache/
.hypothesis/
nosetests.xml
coverage.xml
*.cover
*.py,cover

# Virtual environments. These contain machine-specific binaries and should
# be recreated by each developer via `python -m venv .venv` + `pip install`.
.env
.venv/
venv/
ENV/
env/
env.bak/
venv.bak/


# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 2. Qiskit / Jupyter artifacts and credentials
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Jupyter notebook auto-save checkpoints. Not useful to other developers.
.ipynb_checkpoints/

# IBM Quantum / Qiskit Runtime credential files. These typically live in
# the user's home dir, but if anyone ever drops one into the project by
# accident we want git to refuse to track it.
qiskit-ibm.json
*.qiskit-ibm.json

# Local experiment outputs (plots, serialized results, logs). Safer to
# regenerate from code than to version-control large binary blobs.
results/
outputs/
*.npz
*.npy
*.pkl


# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 3. Project-internal docs (never shipped)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# DESCRIPTION.md is our internal working document: the build plan, the
# architecture reasoning, the decision log, and anything we discuss while
# building the project. It is intentionally NOT public-facing (README.md
# plays that role). Keeping it ignored here has two effects:
#   - `git add .` on dev will never stage it, so it cannot be committed.
#   - Because it is untracked on dev, it cannot propagate to main via the
#     "commit to main" workflow (merge can only move tracked files).
# The file therefore lives only in the developer's working tree.
DESCRIPTION.md


# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 4. Editor / OS noise
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# VS Code / Cursor per-user settings. Keep these local.
.vscode/
.cursor/

# JetBrains IDEs (PyCharm, etc.).
.idea/

# macOS Finder metadata.
.DS_Store

# Windows Explorer metadata.
Thumbs.db
ehthumbs.db
Desktop.ini

# Linux temp files.
*~
